title: Nearly DIED From Car Accident Yesterday.. (Driving With Sleep Deprivation/Drowsiness PSA)
description:
I feel so bad, I'm just extremely remorseful for putting lives other than my own in jeopardy. Driving back home from an amusement, my friend Brandon and I got into the most dangerous situation of our lives. If you are driving and are sleepy or anything of the like, PLEASE pull over. In our case, we were fortunate enough to come out unharmed. But it could've been a lot worse, I just thank God that it wasn't. So while you have the chance, pull over and get the rest you need, lest you might not get the chance if you're too late.

Some facts about driving sleepy/drowsy that I feel you should know: http://drowsydriving.org/about/facts-and-stats/

title: CoryxKenshin: The Return
description:
I've been gone so long it feels weird to even be typing a description..

Anyway, sorry if the video was too talky -- there was so much to say, so many ways to say it, and I just wasn't sure how to. When it's all said and done though, I just wanted to say sorry that I left you all for so long without a word. Without any notice. I needed time away, which there is nothing wrong with, but I didn't let the Samurai know, and that's where I messed up.

I also apologized to my YouTube friends and fellow content creators that felt backlash from my sudden absence. Honestly, I didn't know that would be a repercussion of my leaving. So I'm sorry for the negative ways that affected you all.

I know I've said it before, but if ever there is a time in the future that a similar feeling starts to develop within me that I need to leave for a while, I WILL be letting you know. It's something that I struggle with -- ironically enough I feel like an update like that would be letting a lot of people down, but then NOT saying anything at all is of course letting a lot of people down, most likely more.

So once again, I'm sorry to everyone I let worry, and to everyone I let down. I've got a lot of making up for time to do, so for now I take my leave. I love you all so much. #LongLiveTheSamurai

title: Burnt Out On YouTube!? (Apology to The Samurai)
description:

And so I took a break (obviously you could see by my trash upload schedule) but that I apologized the my manner of taking time away.

From here on out, I will announce when I need to take a few days off. That doesn't mean like twice a month I'm gonna take a break, no I mean every 3-4 months when my YouTube gas tank is depleted, I'll take a few days to recuperate.

title: IT IS COMPLETE! | Building My PC (Part 2)
description:
Hey guys, this would've been up A LONG time ago but upon rendering I noticed a weird "green glitch" that showed up in playback (for example, look closely 2:09). There are actually numerous graphical glitches in this video alone. I re-rendered, altering the settings, ~5 times and to no avail, this green glitch keeps sporadically plaguing me. After doing a little research, I am thinking my [EVGA GTX 970] GPU may be the cause, although have no way to confirm. If ANYONE knows anything about this, please let me know. I use Powerdirector 11 when I render by the way. I'm just ready to be rid of this tomfoolery, ESPECIALLY after building a $2000 brand spanking new machine, highly disappointed right now.

title: Chasing My Dream. (The 'Big' Announcement)
description:
First off, thank you all so much for this crazy opportunity and I just want to say regardless of how you may feel about all this, I considerate it a blessing and am so very grateful for it.

So this is a quick recap for those who couldn't watch the entire video for whatever reason (I know it's a long video, hahah):

1. I am leaving my university for 1 year to do YouTube full-time
2. I will now be uploading every single day at 1:30pm and 3:30pm EST (if I am unable to upload, I will let you all know).
3. If at the end of the year (May 1st, 2016) I have not reached 150,000 subscribers, or feel YouTube isn't a viable living source, I will need to leave YouTube to finish my degree.
4. It was a very tough decision and was thoroughly thought out and I have taken care of all the administrative business to begin this journey.
5. Moving out of my dorm May 1st, 2015 to begin.
6. I DO NOT make a lot of money from YouTube so it will be hard at times I already know.
7. I appreciate the support of all those close to me personally and of course you all. It really means more than the world to me.

So yeah, that's about it. Let's do this, together.

title: CoryxKenshin's Birthday! (+Big news, please watch to end)
description:
A small insight to my life and how grateful I am to you all.

In case you couldn't sit through it all, just expressed three reasons why I'm so blessed to have you all. 

First was the charity work the channel has done. Never imagined I would be able to host such events to help people -- and that makes me immensely happy.

Second is for the fact that I am actually able to financially take care of things thanks to all the support that you guys show my channel by tuning in daily. I know you all cannot directly see the effects of your doing this, but some things have evidently changed for the better in my life due to this.

And third is for being so friendly towards my cause and CoryxKenshin in general. I've never witnessed such kindness from a community on YouTube before so I am happy to be a part of this one.

The big news was I am saving up for moving out of my parents house and getting my own apartment. Again, I never have previously been able to do anything close to this but because of you all and because of YouTube, this is actually becoming a real feasible goal. I will keep you guys updated, just once again thank you.

~CK
